description.narrative: (Rwanda): In FY 2018, through the Rwanda Social Marketing Program (RSMP), USAID will continue to implement social and behavior change and communication (SBCC) activities aimed at improving knowledge of reproductive health, promoting uptake of family planning methods and utilization of maternal and child health services, and supporting malaria prevention and treatment services. The SBCC interventions developed under RSMP will be evidence-based, targeted and cost effective, and will prioritize youth. RSMP will deliver tailored messages through appropriate delivery channels, including community dialogue on various topics, talk shows with health community leaders or subject matter experts, interpersonal communication, drama and mobile video shows depending upon the target audience. RSMP will build on experience from community based organizations, along with proven social marketing tools..RSMP is implemented by the Society for Family Health (SFH) a local partner with strong expertise in delivering health messages to target populations. RSMP directly contributes to the Country Development Cooperation Strategy (CDCS) goal of improving the health and nutrition of Rwandans. .
